'''Kosmos 496''' ({{lang-ru|Космос 496}} meaning ''Cosmos 496'') was an unmanned test of the redesigned [[Soyuz spacecraft|Soyuz]] ferry. It did not dock with any space station. After the [[Soyuz 11]] disaster the third seat was removed because the space was need for the two crewmen in space suits and their equipment. Kosmos 496 retained its solar arrays.
