This is a list of craters on [[Europa (moon)|Europa]]. The surface of [[Jupiter]]'s moon Europa is very young, geologically speaking, and as a result there are very few [[Impact crater|crater]]s. Furthermore, as Europa's surface is potentially made of weak water ice over a liquid ocean, most surviving craters have slumped so that their structure is very low in relief. Most of the craters that are large enough to have names are named after prominent figures in [[Celtic mythology|Celtic myths]] and folklore.

