A '''sentinel outlet''' in [[occupational safety and health]] is a [[Tap (valve)|water outlet]] that is chosen to have its temperature monitored so that risk from ''[[Legionella]]'' can be controlled. This is typically chosen to be the closest and furthest outlets from the [[water tank]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hse.gov.uk/healthservices/legionella.htm|title=Managing legionella in hot and cold water systems|website=www.hse.gov.uk|language=en-GB|access-date=2018-06-28}}</ref>

